  <Markdown>
# Navigator Block Demo

The Navigator block creates a two-pane interface: a searchable list on the left
and detail view on the right. Item data comes from YAML in the block content.
Templates for preview/detail are referenced by block ID.
  </Markdown>

  <Markdown>
## 1. Default Templates

The simplest usage with NavigatorDefaultPreview and NavigatorDefaultDetail:
  </Markdown>

  <Navigator id="default_navigator"
             title="Project Tasks"
             preview="default_preview"
             detail="default_detail">
- id: task1
  title: Research Phase
  subtitle: Week 1-2
  description: Gather background information and review existing literature on the topic.

- id: task2
  title: Data Collection
  subtitle: Week 3-4
  description: Design surveys, conduct interviews, and collect quantitative data.

- id: task3
  title: Analysis
  subtitle: Week 5-6
  description: Process collected data, identify patterns, and draw preliminary conclusions.

- id: task4
  title: Report Writing
  subtitle: Week 7-8
  description: Synthesize findings into a comprehensive final report with recommendations.
  </Navigator>

  <Hidden>
    <NavigatorDefaultPreview id="default_preview"/>
    <NavigatorDefaultDetail id="default_detail"/>
  </Hidden>

  <Markdown>
## 2. Team Templates

